Notebowl Inc. Key Developments

Notebowl and Canvas Announce Partnership
Jun 21 17
Notebowl announced that it is partnering with Canvas that makes teaching and learning easier for educators and students that is used by more than 2,000 universities, school districts and institutions across the world. Notebowl is now making available a seamless integration putting the social learning platform directly inside of Canvas. This integration allows users to access Notebowl at any time using the Notebowl button, and it also includes unique social features for discussion boards, classrooms and communities. The Notebowl and Canvas partnership provides several main points of interoperability that make using Canvas and Notebowl seamless. Those points are: Social News Feed: This new integration brings a news feed style to classrooms and communities, which allows users to post, comment and interact organically. Discussion Boards: Users can create and utilize social discussion boards as assignments, that teachers can easily grade with analytics. Notifications: Personalized notifications are accessible from the homepage and throughout the environment. Communities: Students and teachers now have the ability to create, discover and collaborate with groups, clubs and organizations. Real-time: Assignments, content and grades sync in real-time. Single sign-on: When users are logged into Canvas, they're also logged into Notebowl.


